Welcome to the W3C {{ group.name }}!

Everyone who is involved in the {{ group.name }} is expected to behave in accordance with the W3C Code of Conduct:
  https://www.w3.org/policies/code-of-conduct/

The {{ group.type }} does most of its work on Github and Slack:
  https://www.w3.org/groups/wg/{{ group.shortname }}/tools

If you need an invite to the w3ccommunity Slack, use
  https://www.w3.org/slack-w3ccommunity-invite

The {{ group.type }} is focused on revising its publications:
  https://www.w3.org/groups/wg/{{ group.shortname }}/publications

If you plan to contribute changes to the specifications by providing
pull requests, please link your Github and W3C accounts at:
  https://www.w3.org/users/myprofile/connectedaccounts

The group only meets in Web conferences:
  https://auth.w3.org/?url=https://www.w3.org/groups/wg/{{ group.shortname }}/calendar

Should you have any question on how to get up to speed with the
{{ group.type }}, please get in touch with the W3C Staff Contact of the group:
  Philippe Le Hegaret <plh@w3.org>

Again, warm welcome to the group and to W3C!
